X_n = \frac1n\sum\limits_{i=1}^n\xi_i
\xi_i\in U([0,4])
X_n
\mu = 2
\sigma_n = \frac2{\sqrt{3n}}
\frac{4}{0.03n}\leq 0.01
n\geq\frac{40000}3
 \operatorname{Var}[X_n] = \frac1{n^2}\sum\limits_{i=1}^n\operatorname{Var}[\xi_i] = \frac4{3n}, 
 \mathsf P\left(|X-2|\geq 0.1\right) \leq \frac{\sigma_n^2}{(0.1)^2} = \frac{4}{0.03 n} 
